<p align='center'><font color='#0e024d' face='Arial'><strong>DOT STATEMENT - AUGUST 26, 1999</strong></font></p>
<hr size='1' width='85%'>
<table border='0' width='85%'>
  <tr>
<td valign='top' align='left'><font face='Arial'><small>
Okay, all. I have a bit of info on the change to the DoT's.
<P>I have to tell ya, I play a level 34 Shaman as one of my main characters, and I was very VERY much not happy to hear about this, and I was hoping just as much as some of you that it was a hoax. But it was not a hoax. But at the same time, it's not all bad. Wait before you explode.<P>
<P>I apologize first off for the late response, but I had to get my ducks in a row before I could post anything on this issue. I didn't want to post false info or my own flames for my temper, esp as bad as my temper gets, and since I play a sham and nec primarily, it hurts me tons... or it would.  
<P.The patch to the test server was supposed to make it so that the mob would take no damage if not being engaged in melee by someone or something, meaning another player or pet could melee and the DoT still work. But remember that the test server is just that, a test server. The patch was posted there to test a few alternative ideas concerning kiting.
<P>It is nothing new that kiting is definately not a prefered fighting style by Verant. The first DoT patch cut the DoT cycle time in half and increased damage to compensate (yea, diseases less, but they were too powerful before, so made them similar to like level magics from other classes). They are seeking some way to curb kiting, but to not whipe out so many magics with the changes. This is only a test at this time. Even as posted on many boards and pages, the change going in is still a big IF.
<P>The extent of the change, what will actually be changed, how it will be changed, and when is still in discussion at this time as far as I know. Yes, there are new ideas being tested on the test server, but there is no guarantee that what is on the test server will make it live. So for now, hunting is as normal.
<P>However, you can rest asured that there will indeed be a change of some kind to something to make kiting mobs much harder. To see a character fight a red mob and take zero damage and kill the mob at higher levels is of great concern. Warriors fighting many blues once they reach 20's and 30's take massive damage to do it. But a kiter can take a mob 5 levels higher without a scratch. You can bank on the fact that something will change to help sway this.
<P>Now as to what will change, I have no idea. Maybe they will put more bigger mobs spawning along the normal kiting trails. Maybe they will have red mobs outrun you almost always. Maybe the mob will just stop and no longer chase you. Maybe DoT's will indeed be changed in some way to help curb kiting. Maybe the patch will go in. Maybe it will not. Maybe... Maybe... Maybe...
<P>Noone can say for certain at this moment what will happen, but you can count on something. I think we will still be able to kite the blues a bit, but I have a feeling (totally unofficial) that kiting reds will turn near impossible because of something.
<P>I know some will be hurt to hear that kiting reds will get a twink of some kind, but that is only fair. Warriors can't solo a red without massive damage if at all. Why should some else be able to do it without a scratch or even the possibility of a scratch?
<P>But at this moment, the DoT change on the test server is only a test.
<P>I hope this serves to quench many of the flames for now.
<P>Live strong and Hunt well,
<P><B>- Balstar, Verant Sysop</b>
<P>
<i>This statement taken from the <a href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum12/HTML/000523.html' target='_blank'><b>Everquest Casters Forum</b></a>.</i>

</small></font></p>
